thread.title: From Housing to Stocks, Rising U.S. Bond Yields Are Being Felt

author: Daniel Kruger
title: From Housing to Stocks, Rising U.S. Bond Yields Are Being Felt
text:
Rising U.S. government bond yields are rippling through the economy, affecting everything from mortgage rates to stock performance.
Signs of steady economic growth and expectations for rising inflation have helped push the yield on the benchmark 10-year Treasury note this year to its highest level since 2011, leaving U.S. government bonds paying more than debt from other developed countries.
